Indonesia will host a summit on January 6 to address the aftermath of Asia's natural disaster.
The conference will gather 23 countries, including ASEAN members and international organizations.
Japan has deployed emergency workers to assist in tsunami-hit areas, with a focus on Indonesia.
The death toll in Indonesia has risen to over 94,000, with Sumatra receiving significant aid efforts.
Various countries, including China, Uzbekistan, and Bangladesh, have sent humanitarian aid to the affected regions.
Australia pledged 1 billion Australian dollars in loans and grants for Indonesia's reconstruction.
Japan also committed to long-term support for Aceh and North Sumatra.
